==English==
===Etymology===
'''[[leaf]]''' + '''[[-let]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|lēfʹlĭt}}, {{IPA|/ˈliːflɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/"li:flIt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-leaflet.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|botany}} One of the [[component]]s of a [[compound leaf]].
# {{context|botany}} A [[small]] [[plant]] [[leaf]].
#:''The new '''leaflets''' at the end of the branch were a lighter shade of green than the mature leaves.''
# A small [[sheet]] of [[paper]] containing [[information]], used for [[dissemination]] of said information, often an [[advertisement]].
#:''A '''leaflet''' had been left under the car's [[windshield wiper]].''
#{{context|anatomy}} A [[flap]] of a [[valve]] of a [[heart]] or [[blood vessel]].

